data.chText: （旧时摄影用的）胶片，赛璐珞片
data.enText: a thin transparent plastic material made in sheets, used in the past for cinema film
used as a way of referring to films/movies

means: (旧时摄影用的)胶片，赛璐珞片

tr: a medium that disseminates moving pictures
example: this story would be good cinema

tr: highly flammable substance made from cellulose nitrate and camphor
used in e.g. motion-picture and X-ray film
its use has decreased with the development of nonflammable thermoplastics
artificial as if portrayed in a film
example: a novel with flat celluloid characters

value.def: You can use celluloid to refer to films and the cinema.

example.ex: King's works seem to lack something on celluloid.
example.tran: 金的作品搬上银幕后似乎缺点什么。
